<dl id="n09017b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09017b">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09017b"> 17(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> hoofed animals make their / bellies hives of bacteria to / attack cellulose</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The <mark>hoofed animals</mark> have dealt with this problem in their own way, by <mark>turning their bellies into vast hives of bacteria that attack cellulose</mark>, and on whose by-products they live. We have got to do the same, but outside our bodies. <small> J. B. S. Haldane, <a name="DAED" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#DAED"><cite title="source">Dedalus</cite></a> (1923) 38</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
